你懂我吗?为现金。
Like you got me, huh? For cash.

142
00:15:29,220 --> 00:15:31,139
如果它是必要的。
If it's necessary.

143
00:15:31,222 --> 00:15:38,688
就像我之前说的，琼斯先生，每个人都有自己活着的理由和死的代价。
As I said before, Mr. Jones, each man has his own reason for living and his own price for dying.

144
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:44,068
我希望，对我们所有人来说，这将是一个一路顺风。
I hope, for all of us, that it will be a bon voyage.

145
00:16:00,501 --> 00:16:03,129
乔凡内尔帮他拉线。
Giovanel help him with the line.

146
00:16:05,214 --> 00:16:08,885
Giovanel你!你，卡皮诺，帮他弄鱼雷。
Giovanel you! You, carpino, give him a hand with the torpedo.

147
00:16:11,179 --> 00:16:13,222
你觉得我有几只手，纽曼?
How many hands you think I got, neuman?

148
00:16:13,306 --> 00:16:16,934
你叫纽曼先生。
Mr. Neuman to you.

149
00:16:20,688 --> 00:16:22,833
记得把电池上的读数告诉我。
Now, make sure you give me the reading on that battery.

150
00:16:22,857 --> 00:16:23,691
对了,队长。
Right, skipper.

151
00:16:23,774 --> 00:16:26,819
来吧。来吧!
Come on. Come on!

152
00:16:26,903 --> 00:16:29,780
来吧，伙计们。把它!来吧!
Bring it on, boys. Bring it around! Come on!

153
00:16:29,864 --> 00:16:32,575
嘿，来吧。简单的现在。来吧。
Heyl come on now. Easy now. Come on.

154
00:16:32,658 --> 00:16:35,036
来吧。来吧。好吧,。
Come on. Come on. All right, hold.

155
00:16:35,119 --> 00:16:37,997
好吧,男孩。紧紧抓住防滑钉鞋。
All right, boys. Make it fast to the cleats.

156
00:16:38,998 --> 00:16:42,210
嘿。
Hey.

157
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:52,428
-你从来不洗澡吗?-闭嘴。
- Don't you ever take a bath? - Ah, shut up.

158
00:16:52,512 --> 00:16:55,348
“啊,闭嘴。你的词汇量就这么多吗?
“Ah, shut up.” is that the extent of your vocabulary?

159
00:16:55,431 --> 00:16:57,934
你为什么要放弃摔跤呢?
What'd you ever give up the wrestling racket for anyway?

160
00:16:58,017 --> 00:17:00,978
我刚发现那是假的。
I just found out it was phony.

161
00:17:01,062 --> 00:17:05,167
这就是问题所在……我说，这就是这些假摔跤手的问题所在。
That's the trouble with these... I say, that's the trouble with these phony wrestlers, dugboat.

162
00:17:05,191 --> 00:17:07,693
-他们从不洗澡。-我们也是。
- They never take a bath. - We do too.

163
00:17:13,574 --> 00:17:16,285
嘿,joto。嘿,joto。后阀不转了。
Hey, joto. Hey, joto. The after valve won't turn.

164
00:17:16,369 --> 00:17:18,329
——什么?-后阀不转。
- What? - The after valve won't turn.

165
00:17:18,412 --> 00:17:20,331
不,不。另一种方法。
No, no. The other way.

166
00:17:20,414 --> 00:17:23,793
都反过来了。难怪你们这些家伙会输掉战争，有这样的潜艇。
Everything backwards. No wonder you blokes lost the war, with subs like this.

167
00:17:25,086 --> 00:17:27,004
——队长。-是的。
- Skipper. - Yeah.

168
00:17:27,088 --> 00:17:29,966
-那个叫威尔斯的家伙…任何好吗?-澳大利亚最好的工程师。
- That guy welles... any good? - Best engineer out of Australia.

169
00:17:30,049 --> 00:17:33,302
-要是有威尔伯就好了。-是的。
- Wish we had wilbur. - Yeah.

170
00:17:33,386 --> 00:17:38,224
有了查理·威尔伯操纵船首帆上的引擎，就没什么可担心的了。
With Charlie wilbur handling the engines on the bowfin, there was nothing to worry about.

171
00:17:38,307 --> 00:17:40,977
听说他现在是脱衣舞娘了。
Hear he's a three-striper now.

172
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:42,979
是的，我听说了。
Yeah, so I hear.

173
00:17:43,062 --> 00:17:45,565
船长，二号瞄准器坏了。
Skipper, that number two scopes don't work.

174
00:17:45,648 --> 00:17:48,109
-怎么了?-没办法把锈去掉。
- What's the matter with it? - Can't get the rust out of it.

175
00:17:48,192 --> 00:17:50,152
-第一名怎么样?-我没检查。
- How 'bout number one? - Didn't check it.

176
00:17:50,236 --> 00:17:52,238
把她抬起来，动态心电图。
Lift her up, holter.

177
00:17:57,285 --> 00:18:00,204
上面的教授要见船长。
The professor topside wants to see the captain.

178
00:18:00,288 --> 00:18:02,206
让他下来。
Send him down.

179
00:18:02,290 --> 00:18:04,792
他是幕后黑手。
He's part of the brass behind this setup.

180
00:18:04,875 --> 00:18:07,503
如果他看起来很眼熟，什么都别说。稍后我将解释。
Now, if he looks familiar, don't say anything. I'll explain later.

181
00:18:09,005 --> 00:18:12,842
你好,教授。欢迎登机，长官-船长。
- Hello, professor. Welcome aboard, sir. - Captain.

182
00:18:12,925 --> 00:18:18,014
好吧，我们试着用一点口水和大量的汗水把这个下水管道组装起来。
Well, we're trying to put this sewer pipe together with a little spit and a lot of sweat.

183
00:18:18,097 --> 00:18:20,641
-我想我们会解决的。-琼斯上尉。
- I guess we'll make it all right. - Captain Jones.

184
00:18:20,725 --> 00:18:23,144
有什么事吗?有什么问题吗?
What's the matter? Is there something wrong?

185
00:18:23,227 --> 00:18:27,565
很抱歉，我们不能允许你的船员参加这次探险。
I'm sorry to say we cannot permit one of your crew to make this expedition.

186
00:18:27,648 --> 00:18:29,859
你是什么意思?他们都是精心挑选的。
What do you mean? They were all handpicked.

187
00:18:29,942 --> 00:18:31,861
-我们不能相信这个。——谁?
- We cannot trust this one. - Who?

188
00:18:31,944 --> 00:18:33,779
鱼雷手，雷夫尼克。
The torpedo man, revnik.

189
00:18:33,863 --> 00:18:35,781
你选的人之一。
Oh, one of the men you picked.

190
00:18:35,865 --> 00:18:39,368
我本可以一直告诉你的。knothead。
I could have told you that all the time. A knothead.

191
00:18:39,452 --> 00:18:42,538
你也检查了我所有的人吗?
Did you screen all my men too?

192
00:18:42,622 --> 00:18:46,042
非常亲密，包括你。
Very closely, including you.

193
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:48,836
——好的。我马上把莱夫尼克处理掉。——好。
- Okay. I'll get rid of revnik right away. - Good.

194
00:18:48,919 --> 00:18:50,838
霍尔特,我希望……
Holter, I want...

195
00:19:04,185 --> 00:19:06,812
她是替补吗，医生?
She the replacement, doc?

196
00:19:06,896 --> 00:19:11,442
先生们，这是杰勒德教授，我的助手，我的得力助手。
Gentlemen, this is professor Gerard, my assistant and my right arm.

197
00:19:11,525 --> 00:19:14,612
-你好。-丹尼斯，这是琼斯队长。
- Hiya. - Denise, this is captain Jones.

198
00:19:14,695 --> 00:19:17,490
-琼斯上尉。-很高兴认识你，教授。
- Captain Jones. - Glad to know you, professor.

199
00:19:17,573 --> 00:19:20,910
如果我知道这件事，我就会降价了。
Well, if I'd known about this, I'd have cut my price.

200
00:19:20,993 --> 00:19:23,871
伙计们，这两位教授要跟我们一起去。
Boys, these two professors are going with us as cargo.

201
00:19:23,954 --> 00:19:25,873
——什么?-你听到了。
- What? - You heard me.

202
00:19:25,956 --> 00:19:29,001
你的垫圈爆了吗?没人会把女人带上船。
Have you blown a gasket? Nobody takes a female along in a pigboat.

203
00:19:29,085 --> 00:19:33,798
听着，小子，你要跟我说他们是坏运气吗?
Look, junior, you gonna give me that 2,000-year-Old Navy bilge that they're bad luck?

204
00:19:33,881 --> 00:19:36,509
看看她。这有什么不好的?
Take a look at her. What's so bad about that?

205
00:19:36,592 --> 00:19:43,015
一文不值。完全没有啊，他们都是约拿。它的传统。
Nothin'. Absolutely nothin'i ah, they're all Jonahs. It's traditional.

206
00:19:46,477 --> 00:19:48,979
船长，我已经决定了。别把我算在内。
Look, skipper, I made up my mind. Count me out.

207
00:19:50,648 --> 00:19:52,858
好吧。
Okay.

208
00:19:52,942 --> 00:19:54,860
还有人吗?
Anybody else?

209
00:19:56,362 --> 00:20:03,411
我给你们五分钟时间好好想想，记住，如果有必要，我可以把你们每个人都换掉。
I'll give you jokers five minutes to sleep on it, and remember, iflhaveto, I can replace every one of you.

210
00:20:03,494 --> 00:20:06,038
队长，我也不喜欢这样。
Captain, I do not like it either.

211
00:20:18,968 --> 00:20:20,302
哦,scusami。
Oh, scusami.

212
00:20:22,430 --> 00:20:24,390
也许你是对的。
Perhaps you are right.

213
00:20:24,473 --> 00:20:28,477
在你看来，我是一个…一个女性。
In your estimation, I am a... a female.

214
00:20:28,561 --> 00:20:31,439
但首先我是个科学家，是个好科学家。
But first I am a scientist and a good one.

215
00:20:31,522 --> 00:20:35,192
我不是唯一一个非你们性别的科学家。
And I am not the only scientist who is not of your sex.

216
00:20:35,276 --> 00:20:37,319
有很多。
There are many.

217
00:20:37,403 --> 00:20:43,743
比如Lise meitner博士，他在原子弹的研制中发挥了重要作用。
Like Dr. Lise meitner, who played an important part in the development of the atom bomb.

218
00:20:43,826 --> 00:20:47,371
比如发现镭的居里夫人。
Like madame curie, who discovered radium.

219
00:20:47,455 --> 00:20:50,875
我是在实验室里长大的。
I have grown up in laboratories.

220
00:20:50,958 --> 00:20:53,669
我这辈子都在和男人打交道。
All my life, I have worked with men.

221
00:20:53,753 --> 00:20:58,841
我从来没有干涉过他们，他们也从来没有怨恨过我。
Never have I interfered, and never have they resented me.

222
00:21:00,384 --> 00:21:05,097
montel教授和我…有很多事情要完成。
Professor montel and I have... Have much to accomplish.

223
00:21:05,181 --> 00:21:07,725
多。
Much.

224
00:21:07,808 --> 00:21:17,276
如果你不让我的…我的出现是…一场小叛乱。
And I shall appreciate it if you would not let my... my presence be the cause of... of a minor mutiny.

225
00:21:33,083 --> 00:21:35,002
我喜欢你。
I like you.

226
00:21:36,003 --> 00:21:38,005
我喜欢你们所有人。
I like you all.

227
00:21:39,715 --> 00:21:42,635
我会尽我最大的努力让你喜欢我……
And I shall try my best to make you like me...

228
00:21:45,805 --> 00:21:47,807
作为一个科学家。
As a scientist.

229
00:21:57,483 --> 00:22:00,736
天啊，这对一个女人来说太拗口了!
Man, that was quite a mouthful for a female!

230
00:22:00,820 --> 00:22:04,406
这是没有女性。这是一个科学家!
That's no female. That's a scientist!

231
00:22:04,490 --> 00:22:07,159
好吧。来吧。我们还有很多工作要做。我们走吧。
All right. Come on. We got a lot of work to do. Let's go.

232
00:22:14,375 --> 00:22:17,920
嗨，藤森先生，教授。
Hi, Mr. Fujimori, professor.

233
00:22:18,003 --> 00:22:20,923
-你的助理呢?-你准备好起航了吗?
- Where's your assistant? - Are you prepared to sail?

234
00:22:21,006 --> 00:22:23,801
明天我们进行潜泳测试后我再通知你。
I'll let you know tomorrow after we make the running dive tests.

235
00:22:23,884 --> 00:22:25,803
我们已经没有明天了。
There's no tomorrow left for us.

236
00:22:25,886 --> 00:22:28,389
江青号货轮半小时前从天津启航了。
The freighter kiang ching sailed from tientsin a half hour ago.

237
00:22:28,472 --> 00:22:30,766
-你必须马上离开。-你在说什么?
- You must leave right away. - What are you talking about?

238
00:22:30,850 --> 00:22:35,104
我们才工作了两个星期。这个浴缸还有很多工作要做。
We only been working for two weeks. We've got a lot of work left to do on this tub.

239
00:22:35,187 --> 00:22:38,274
你必须在天黑前离开，才能赶上她。-正在进行的测试呢?
- You must leave by dark to overtake her. - What about the running tests?

240
00:22:38,357 --> 00:22:43,821
作为一个业余爱好者，我建议我们在跑步的时候试试跑步测试?
As an amateur, might I suggest that we try the running test while we are running?

241
00:22:43,904 --> 00:22:46,740
博士，失去潜艇的方法有上百种。
Doc, there are about a hundred ways of losing a submarine.

242
00:22:46,824 --> 00:22:48,784
你刚刚想出了最好的一个。
You've just come up with one of the best.

243
00:22:48,868 --> 00:22:50,870
我们还没检查鱼雷发射管呢。
We haven't even checked the torpedo tubes yet.

244
00:22:50,953 --> 00:22:54,498
你知道如果我们要叫鱼的话意味着什么吗?这意味着我们死了。
You know what that means if we have to call on fish? It means we're dead.

245
00:22:54,582 --> 00:22:56,584
你今晚必须离开。
You've got to leave tonight.

246
00:22:58,085 --> 00:23:01,130
好吧，老兄，这次旅行你买了。你想让我试试吗?
Okay, buster, you're buying this trip. You want me to chance it?

247
00:23:01,213 --> 00:23:04,008
这不是我们想要的，琼斯上尉。这是必须要做的。
It's not what we want, captain Jones. It's what must be done.

248
00:23:04,091 --> 00:23:07,678
好吧。只要这位教授知道他是为了什么才进来的。
All right. Just as long as the professor here knows what he's letting himself in for.

249
00:23:07,761 --> 00:23:10,490
我们已经安排飞机联系，告诉你江清的位置。
We've arranged airplane contact to give you position on the kiang ching.

250
00:23:10,514 --> 00:23:13,309
-他们怎么联系我们，用信号灯还是无线电?-两者都不是没有风险的。
- How'll they contact us, blinker or radio? - Neither is without risk.

251
00:23:13,392 --> 00:23:16,353
我们认为掉软木塞最安全。
We've decided cork drop is safest.

252
00:23:16,437 --> 00:23:21,692
这包含您的代码，这包含您的联系人日程安排。
This contains your code, and this contains your schedule for contacts.

253
00:23:21,775 --> 00:23:24,153
哦，还有一件事。
Oh, just one more thing.

254
00:23:24,236 --> 00:23:28,574
我需要一个明确的指示，详细说明我的具体权力。
I want a clear-cut directive detailing my specific authority.

255
00:23:28,657 --> 00:23:31,035
都在这里，船长。
You'll find it all in here, captain.

256
00:23:31,118 --> 00:23:33,495
在海上，完全由你指挥。
At sea, you are in complete command.

257
00:23:33,579 --> 00:23:37,166
在陆地上，蒙泰尔教授负责指挥。
On land, professor montel is in command.

258
00:23:37,249 --> 00:23:40,628
我能祝你好运吗?
May I wish you the best of luck?

259
00:23:40,711 --> 00:23:42,630
谢谢。
Thanks.

260
00:24:11,033 --> 00:24:13,702
现在正是时候，纽曼先生。
Well, now's as good a time as any, Mr. Neuman.

261
00:24:13,786 --> 00:24:16,664
-把她带到潜望镜深度。——是的,先生。
- Take her down to periscope depth. - Yes, sir.

262
00:24:16,747 --> 00:24:18,749
清晰的桥梁!
Clear the bridge!

263
00:24:21,460 --> 00:24:24,129
潜水!
Dive!

264
00:24:36,600 --> 00:24:39,228
站在那边。你会没事的。
Stand right over there. You'll be all right.

265
00:24:39,311 --> 00:24:42,898
——谢谢。-杰勒德教授，把手给我。
- Thank you. - Professor Gerard, give me your hand.

266
00:24:42,982 --> 00:24:46,068
注意顶端的横档。这是谋杀。
Watch that top rung. It's murder.

267
00:24:46,151 --> 00:24:48,070
——谢谢。——欢迎你。
- Thank you. - You're welcome.

268
00:24:48,153 --> 00:24:50,072
你坐在这里。
You sit right here.

269
00:24:50,155 --> 00:24:52,157
船长，在潜望镜深度修整完毕。
Captain, trim satisfactory at periscope depth.

270
00:24:52,241 --> 00:24:54,159
- - - - - -很好。Joto。——是的,先生?
- Very well. Joto. - Yes, sir?

271
00:24:54,243 --> 00:24:56,972
帮威尔斯把右舷引擎的蓝图翻译一下，好吗?
Give welles a hand with those starboard engine blueprint translations, will you?

272
00:24:56,996 --> 00:24:58,914
我会处理的，队长。
I'll take care of it, captain.

273
00:24:58,998 --> 00:25:01,208
fonnard鱼雷室一切都很紧张。
Everything's tight in the fonnard torpedo room.

274
00:25:01,291 --> 00:25:04,378
我们要把她弄到深处去。检查所有站点。让我知道。
We're gonna try her down deep. Have all stations checked. Let me know.

275
00:25:04,461 --> 00:25:06,755
哦,是的,队长。
Ay, ay, captain.

276
00:25:06,839 --> 00:25:10,175
这就是我们今天谈到的测试，教授。
This is that test we were talking about today, professor.

277
00:25:10,259 --> 00:25:12,845
——现在?——现在。
- Now? - Now.

278
00:25:12,928 --> 00:25:16,598
不要紧张。如果我们崩溃了，你就没机会感受了。
Don't get nervous. If we crack up, you won't get a chance to feel it.

279
00:25:16,682 --> 00:25:18,600
不要着急。没事的。
Take it easy. It'll be all right.

280
00:25:18,684 --> 00:25:20,686
把她放在下面，纽曼先生。
Put her on the bottom, Mr. Neuman.

281
00:25:20,769 --> 00:25:22,771
下降2度。
Two degrees down bubble.

282
00:25:24,023 --> 00:25:26,608
——洪水负面。——洪水负面。
- Flood negative. - Flood negative.

283
00:25:33,782 --> 00:25:36,326
哦，谢谢，李成。
Oh, thanks, chin Lee.

284
00:25:36,410 --> 00:25:38,412
咖啡,教授?——不,谢谢。
- Coffee, professor? - No, thanks.

285
00:25:38,495 --> 00:25:40,998
-你呢?-不用了，谢谢。
- How 'bout you? - No, thank you.

286
00:25:48,464 --> 00:25:50,466
两百英尺，卡比塔先生。
Two hundred feet, kapita'n.

287
00:26:01,310 --> 00:26:03,312
最好等一下，教授。
Better hold on, professor.

288
00:26:33,175 --> 00:26:35,677
好吧。现在我们来看看能不能冲上屋顶。
All right. Now let's see if we can hit the roof.

289
00:26:35,761 --> 00:26:38,514
-把她抬上去，纽曼先生。-关闭所有主压载通风口。
